  "description": [
    "ON TO NEW YORK TROGRESS OF THE CORTEGE Ne PROGRESS OF THE CORTEGE General Grants Remains Viewed by 60000 People at Albany Departure from the Capital and Arrival at New York By telegraph to the Dispatch 10 oclock this morning sixty thousand persons had viewed the remains of General Grant From early morming throngs of strangers who had found places for watching the funeral proces son maintained their positions upon steps and porticos and awnings and curbstones Guns were fired early and all through the forenoon the heavy booming at intervals bore to the crowds the added suggestion of the occasion that had drawn then together It is estimated that one hundred thousand strangers are in the old Irutch city Field pieces and limbers drawn by powerful horses rolled throwgh the streets to Capitol Park and mounted of ficers and their trappings were eonspic uous in the streets Business was par tially suspended A committee from New York about fifty members of which were present at the meeting this morning was presided over by exGov ernor Cornell A letter from Mayor Grace was read stating that the funds to provide for the expenses of the committee have been obtained and"
